HEADWORD: Chondrigen
<hw>Chon"dri*gen</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr.
<grk>cho`ndros</grk> cartilage + <ets>-gen</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Physiol.
Chem.)</fld> <def>The chemical basis of cartilage, converted by long
boiling in water into a gelatinous body called chondrin.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Chondrigenous</ent>⟦br⟧
